First and foremost : a `Publisher` is the parent class of `Mono` and `Flux`. It is defined in [reactivestream API](https://javadoc.io/doc/org.reactivestreams/reactive-streams/latest/org/reactivestreams/Publisher.html) as the value producer (the stream source). A `Mono` is a specialization that sends 0 or 1 element, and a Flux is a specialization that sends 0 to many elements.

Also, generally, a publisher is not triggered  until subscription (subscribe() or block()). Generally, in a Spring app, the flux or Mono is propagated to the web (your rest controller or request router) or database layer (reactive/r2dbc repository), which will be responsible for subscribing to the flux.
Although, you are still allowed to subscribe yourself, but then it becomes your responsibility to consume elements and schedule tasks on the right [Scheduler](https://projectreactor.io/docs/core/release/api/reactor/core/scheduler/Schedulers.html).

