List&lt;Runnable&gt; runnableList = List.of(
        unchecked(() -&gt; doSomething()),
        unchecked(() -&gt; doSomething()),
        // ...
        unchecked(() -&gt; doSomething())
);
```
Any exception (including unchecked exceptions) are wrapped in instances of `CheckedException`, so to get those back you&#39;d need to catch this exception and retrieve its cause.

